WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:07.746
What would you want to say
to the man who assaulted you?

00:07.790 --> 00:10.401
Everyone should know your name.
It's Peter Benoit.

00:10.445 --> 00:13.317
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:13.361 --> 00:16.407
It's amazing. It's exactly
what the world needs right now.

00:16.451 --> 00:18.714
Jane: We would like to
invite you to be the guest host

00:18.757 --> 00:20.846
while we look for Dr. Stacy's
permanent replacement.

00:20.890 --> 00:22.718
Gary:
I've got Darcy and Liam,

00:22.761 --> 00:24.763
but I feel like
I don't deserve any of it.

00:24.807 --> 00:26.548
I'm sorry I didn't answer
last night.

00:26.591 --> 00:28.419
Where were you?
My dad's.

00:28.463 --> 00:30.378
We can never meet
like this again.

00:30.421 --> 00:32.075
Here I am,
fresh off an interview

00:32.119 --> 00:34.730
for head chef
at Crocodilze.

00:34.773 --> 00:37.298
I got a call
from the person who hit me.

00:37.341 --> 00:40.040
Obsessing about it like this
is keeping you in the past.

00:40.083 --> 00:42.085
Saunders: You were pretty upset
the other day at the station.

00:42.129 --> 00:43.826
The next day, this guy's
in the hospital.

00:43.869 --> 00:45.915
Eventually he's gonna
wake up, and when he does,

00:45.958 --> 00:48.831
he can tell us himself
what happened.

00:49.875 --> 00:51.094
[ Horn honks ]

00:51.138 --> 00:53.401
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:53.444 --> 00:55.185
[ Ominous music plays ]

00:55.229 --> 00:57.535
♪♪

00:57.579 --> 00:59.276
[ Engine shuts off ]

00:59.320 --> 01:01.757
♪♪

01:01.800 --> 01:03.019
[ Car door closes ]

01:03.063 --> 01:04.673
You looking for tips
on how to be a dog walker?

01:04.716 --> 01:06.109
Bring a second bag.

01:06.153 --> 01:08.111
Mornings tend to be
two-poop walks.

01:08.155 --> 01:10.548
Sit for me, pal.

01:10.592 --> 01:12.376
I have to ask you
a few more questions.

01:12.420 --> 01:13.812
[ Scoffs ]
Man, if you still think

01:13.856 --> 01:16.250
I had something to do with
that Peter guy getting hurt,

01:16.293 --> 01:20.123
then you and my boy Colin
are full of the same thing.

01:20.167 --> 01:23.909
So tell me --
do either you or Colin...

01:23.953 --> 01:25.781
know somebody named
Christopher Gregory?

01:25.824 --> 01:27.870
I can't speak for Colin...

01:27.913 --> 01:31.265
'cause Colin can't speak
for Colin, but, uh, no.

01:31.308 --> 01:32.744
No, that name
doesn't ring a bell.

01:32.788 --> 01:36.183
Really? Huh.
That's weird.

01:36.226 --> 01:39.751
How often do you let
someone you don't know...

01:39.795 --> 01:41.797
ride in the car with you?

01:43.625 --> 01:45.279
Oh. Topher!

01:45.322 --> 01:49.370
I had no idea that his last name
was, what, Gregory?

01:49.413 --> 01:51.981
What were the two of you guys
doing together the other day?

01:52.024 --> 01:53.896
Uh, you know,
he saw me out with my dog.

01:53.939 --> 01:55.463
He wanted to surprise me.

01:55.506 --> 01:57.334
Kind of like
you just did.

01:57.378 --> 02:01.077
Don't be upset that I was
way happier to see him, okay?

02:01.121 --> 02:03.993
Apparently Peter may have done
something similar to his kid.

02:04.036 --> 02:05.908
Small world, huh?

02:05.951 --> 02:08.128
Is it? That guy taught music
to half of Boston.

02:08.171 --> 02:10.260
I'm sure the list
is longer than two.

02:10.304 --> 02:13.263
Hm. That's
an interesting theory.

02:13.307 --> 02:14.743
Here's mine.

02:15.874 --> 02:17.180
I think you were so upset

02:17.224 --> 02:19.269
that we couldn't press charges
against Peter

02:19.313 --> 02:21.793
that after you gave
my trash can a face-lift,

02:21.837 --> 02:24.187
you decided to do something
with that anger,

02:24.231 --> 02:26.885
so you went over
to Layla's dad's house.

02:26.929 --> 02:29.366
Now, in my version,
you didn't know the guy,

02:29.410 --> 02:31.977
but if you're close enough
to call him Topher,

02:32.021 --> 02:34.458
my theory
works even better.

02:34.502 --> 02:37.592
You convinced him to go with you
over to Peter's place,

02:37.635 --> 02:40.072
but when you saw the guy
who did those horrible things

02:40.116 --> 02:43.424
to Sophie and Layla,
something in you snapped.

02:43.467 --> 02:45.643
Your anger
got the best of you.

02:45.687 --> 02:48.472
And maybe you did
the same thing to Peter

02:48.516 --> 02:50.431
that you did
to my trash can.

02:50.474 --> 02:51.997
[ Chuckles ]

02:52.041 --> 02:54.957
That is, uh...
very entertaining.

02:56.480 --> 02:58.787
I feel like I saw it
on "The Rookie," though.

02:58.830 --> 03:00.963
Nathan Fillion
knocked it out of the park.

03:01.006 --> 03:02.834
He should get another
People's Choice Award for it.

03:02.878 --> 03:05.359
[ Clears throat ]

03:05.402 --> 03:10.755
I told you. I was watching
"Jeopardy!" at my dad's, okay?

03:10.799 --> 03:12.844
I have no idea
where Topher was,

03:12.888 --> 03:14.933
but I'm sure
it wasn't at Peter's.

03:14.977 --> 03:17.893
So it's our word against --

03:17.936 --> 03:21.244
Oh, that's right --
no word.

03:21.288 --> 03:23.899
Actually,
it appears that, uh...

03:23.942 --> 03:25.901
Peter's out of his coma.

03:25.944 --> 03:28.556
I'm gonna head over
to the hospital to
talk to him right now.

03:28.599 --> 03:31.950
So it'll be your word...
against his.

03:33.517 --> 03:35.215
Great.

03:35.258 --> 03:37.391
Saunders:
Enjoy the fresh air.

03:37.434 --> 03:39.436
Get it while you can, pal.

03:39.480 --> 03:42.744
♪♪

03:42.787 --> 03:44.224
[ Car door closes ]

03:44.267 --> 03:46.051
--Captions by VITAC--

03:46.095 --> 03:48.967
Brought to you by: Ford,
Built Ford Proud

03:57.672 --> 03:58.847
Who was that?

03:58.890 --> 04:00.022
[ Horn honks in distance ]

04:00.065 --> 04:02.459
Oh. That --Isn't that the guy

04:02.503 --> 04:04.548
that brought the puck
back to us the other day?

04:04.592 --> 04:08.465
God. Good memory. Yeah.
I-I guess we inspired him.

04:08.509 --> 04:10.293
He and his kid have been
playing street hockey,

04:10.337 --> 04:12.730
and he dropped by
to see if you and I

04:12.774 --> 04:14.602
wanted a little
two-on-two action.

04:14.645 --> 04:17.648
But I had to tell him this
franchise is moving to Lenox,

04:17.692 --> 04:19.346
so no can do.Hm.

04:19.389 --> 04:21.217
Well, we're gonna
go run some errands,

04:21.261 --> 04:23.132
grab some burgers for lunch.
You in?

04:23.175 --> 04:27.005
I'm gonna feed thisboy so that
he doesn't eat our burgers,

04:27.049 --> 04:29.530
but, uh, why don't you grab 'em
and I'll meet you back here?

04:29.573 --> 04:31.183
And can we not do
the thing where we --

04:31.227 --> 04:32.924
Share one order of fries?Yeah.

04:32.968 --> 04:34.883
Would you listen
to your men, please?

04:34.926 --> 04:36.276
We speak
the same language.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.103
Fine. Fine.
Three orders of fries.

04:38.147 --> 04:39.235
You want to make 'em
sweet potato?

04:39.279 --> 04:40.671
[ Scoffs ] Boo!
Boo!

04:40.715 --> 04:42.064
[ Chuckles ]

04:42.107 --> 04:43.326
[ Both imitate explosion ]Okay.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.676
Let's go. [ Chuckles ]
We'll see you later.

04:45.720 --> 04:49.245
Liam: Don't try to make me
eat a yam by calling it a fry.

04:49.289 --> 04:50.899
Maggie: Oh, my God.

04:50.942 --> 04:53.075
Do you have to have an August
birthday to get a job here?

04:53.118 --> 04:55.512
I mean, this is like my fourth
slice of cake this week.

04:55.556 --> 04:57.340
I'm not complaining.
I'm just saying.

04:57.384 --> 04:59.124
Or you could
just not eat it.

04:59.168 --> 05:01.779
Hm. Okay. [ Scoffs ]

05:01.823 --> 05:03.781
[ Chuckles ] Listen, Maggie.

05:03.825 --> 05:05.217
Tomorrow's your last day.

05:05.261 --> 05:06.697
So when Jane gets here...

05:06.741 --> 05:08.525
Don't worry. I've got
my whole speech prepared.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.875
Jane is going to know that
I want the job permanently.

05:10.919 --> 05:13.922
Good, 'cause I want
myjob permanently.

05:13.965 --> 05:15.750
These last two weeks
have been so incredible,

05:15.793 --> 05:17.708
and that is not just
the cake talking.

05:17.752 --> 05:19.319
This cake is so good!

05:19.362 --> 05:21.103
[ Door opens ]Jane: Knock, knock!

05:21.146 --> 05:22.322
What are you guys
talking about?

05:22.365 --> 05:24.367
[ Chuckles ]
[Hushed] Don't say cake.

05:24.411 --> 05:26.630
Actually, Jane,
if you have a second,

05:26.674 --> 05:28.676
there's something that I wanted
to speak with you about.

05:28.719 --> 05:30.939
Oh, check it out. Jane's
slummin' with the common people.

05:30.982 --> 05:32.767
Look out for a fat guy in
a red suit, everyone,

05:32.810 --> 05:34.246
'cause this must be
the Christmas party.

05:34.290 --> 05:36.945
Charming as ever, Nick.
I actually dropped by

05:36.988 --> 05:38.860
to thank you for giving up
your personal hygiene

05:38.903 --> 05:40.949
in order to make it
into the office on time.

05:40.992 --> 05:43.212
[ Gasps ] Ooh!
Love the sweat pants.

05:43.255 --> 05:46.389
Nothing says "I care about work"
more than an elastic waistband.

05:46.433 --> 05:48.086
You know, you might want
to use your lunch hour

05:48.130 --> 05:49.392
to go get another shot
of Botox.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.394
Your forehead almost moved
when you said that.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.396
You know what goes great
with cake?

05:53.440 --> 05:56.312
Is whatever beverage
is out here.

05:56.356 --> 05:58.445
Claudia:
I'll pour it for you!

05:58.488 --> 06:00.360
[ Exhales deeply ]
Oh, my gosh. Thank you.

06:00.403 --> 06:02.231
Had to be done. I'm gonna
go ahead in the break room.

06:02.274 --> 06:04.929
Hey. Uh, I don't think
we've met. I'm Maggie.

06:04.973 --> 06:08.280
Hi. That's right. Y-You've been
taking over for Dr. Stacy.

06:08.324 --> 06:09.891
I'm Rachel Frumaychar.

06:09.934 --> 06:12.023
[ Sniffs ] Mmm! Wow.

06:12.067 --> 06:13.460
I just started
brewing a cup.

06:13.503 --> 06:15.331
It'll just be a few
more seconds.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.985
Unless -- Do you need me
to stop it?

06:17.028 --> 06:20.510
N-No. No. I'm just --
I'm killing time.

06:20.554 --> 06:23.295
A little piece of advice --
avoid the booth right now.

06:23.339 --> 06:26.429
I just dodged another awkward
fight between Nick and Jane.

06:26.473 --> 06:28.779
Talk about a hostile work
environment.

06:28.823 --> 06:31.695
Oh.
Thanks for the tip.

06:31.739 --> 06:33.349
Yeah.

06:33.393 --> 06:36.047
Mmm!

06:36.091 --> 06:38.659
Oh, you've got to be kidding me!

06:38.702 --> 06:40.182
Ooh, is that red velvet?

06:40.225 --> 06:42.489
Cindy, right?
Happy birthday!

06:42.532 --> 06:45.448
Tell your mother
we said hello

06:45.492 --> 06:47.145
and congratulations
once again, young man.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.277
Ah. Wait.
Was that Tyrell?[ Beeps ]

06:48.320 --> 06:50.235
Mm-hmm.
Oh. Is he excited?

06:50.279 --> 06:52.194
Excited that our
documentary got chosen

06:52.237 --> 06:54.326
by the New England Film
Institute for the festival?

06:54.370 --> 06:57.112
Yeah! Yeah. Yep.[ Cellphone vibrating ]

06:57.155 --> 07:00.115
Oh, wait. Oh, wait. That's --
That's my agent calling.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.769
Joel, my man.
What's the word?

07:01.812 --> 07:03.771
I just got off the phone
with Paragon Plus.

07:03.814 --> 07:06.295
They saw your documentary
was an official selection

07:06.338 --> 07:09.037
in the film festival, and they
requested an early screening.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.821
If you're calling for my
permission to give it to them,

07:10.865 --> 07:12.910
give it to them. Way ahead of you, man.

07:12.954 --> 07:14.869
They dropped everything
and watched it right away.

07:14.912 --> 07:17.175
That's why I'm calling.
They loved it.

07:17.219 --> 07:18.394
Oh, my God.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.048
And they want to buy it.Oh, my God!

07:20.091 --> 07:22.572
Yeah, my wife might be listening
in on our conversation.

07:22.616 --> 07:23.965
[ Chuckles ]
Hi! [ Chuckles ]

07:24.008 --> 07:25.488
Oh, good.
Listen to this.

07:25.532 --> 07:26.924
If they're buying it
preemptively,

07:26.968 --> 07:28.665
the offer's gonna be big.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.406
I'm supposed to call
their business-affairs person

07:30.450 --> 07:31.581
right now.

07:31.625 --> 07:33.801
Are you okay
if I sell your movie?

07:33.844 --> 07:35.716
He is. Oh.

07:35.759 --> 07:37.413
[ Laughs ] I am. Come here.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.807
Great.
I'll call you both back later.

07:39.850 --> 07:41.765
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:41.809 --> 07:43.593
Hm! Rome Howard.
Hm?

07:43.637 --> 07:46.335
You sold your movie.I sold my movie.

07:46.378 --> 07:49.077
I am not surprised
at all.

07:49.120 --> 07:50.818
Ohh. Thank you, Gina.
Ohh.

07:50.861 --> 07:52.602
Just...thank you. Come here.

07:52.646 --> 07:55.257
And tonight...
I want to celebrate.

07:55.300 --> 07:56.780
Why we gotta wait
till tonight?

07:56.824 --> 07:58.521
We can --
We can celebrate right now!

07:58.565 --> 08:00.436
Because I have to go make

08:00.480 --> 08:02.656
40 orders
of chicken nuggets

08:02.699 --> 08:05.485
which may or may not actually
contain chicken,

08:05.528 --> 08:08.183
and you are supposed to
have lunch with your father.

08:08.226 --> 08:10.315
Who may or may not contain
nurturing qualities.

08:10.359 --> 08:11.534
[ Chuckles ]

08:11.578 --> 08:12.840
You sold your movie.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.972
[Softly]
I sold my movie.

08:15.016 --> 08:17.584
I'm proud of you.I-I'm just
gonna play it cool.

08:17.627 --> 08:19.586
I'm gonna play it cool!

08:19.629 --> 08:21.413
[ Laughs ]

08:22.937 --> 08:26.549
She said she wants
to meet with me.

08:26.593 --> 08:29.117
[ Chuckles ] I mean,
what could she possibly say

08:29.160 --> 08:30.727
that's gonna make
any of this okay?

08:30.771 --> 08:34.035
Oh, I know --
maybe shegets to be the one

08:34.078 --> 08:35.950
to tell my son that
I'm never gonna walk again.

08:35.993 --> 08:37.386
[ Ball bounces ]

08:37.429 --> 08:39.562
Yeah, well,
someone's gonna have to.

08:39.606 --> 08:42.086
Really?
You'repiling on me now?

08:42.130 --> 08:44.436
Look. I thought I made it clear
when I started working with you.

08:44.480 --> 08:47.614
I'm never gonna make
pleasing you my goal.

08:47.657 --> 08:50.094
I'm gonna make helping you
move on with your life my goal,

08:50.138 --> 08:53.402
which hopefully willplease you,
but there is a difference.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.230
[ Sighs ]

08:58.407 --> 09:00.583
Look, Eddie,
I-I know what I said before,

09:00.627 --> 09:04.021
but if it's bothering you
this much...

09:04.065 --> 09:05.588
you should meet with her.

09:07.068 --> 09:08.504
Don't spend any more
of your life

09:08.548 --> 09:11.115
obsessing over
what happened that night.

09:11.159 --> 09:12.290
♪♪

09:12.334 --> 09:15.206
Hear what she has to say...

09:15.250 --> 09:16.730
so you can actually
move on.

09:16.773 --> 09:22.126
♪♪

09:22.170 --> 09:24.651
[ Bell jingles ]Christopher: Thank you, ma'am.
Let me just grab that for you.

09:26.217 --> 09:27.479
Topher.

09:27.523 --> 09:29.351
Oh, my God, man!
Is that you?!

09:31.658 --> 09:33.660
Hello, sir.
Uh, how can I help you?

09:33.703 --> 09:37.054
"Sir." Listen to this guy.
Toph! It's me!

09:37.098 --> 09:40.580
Get over here, man.
Come in for a squeeze. Grr!

09:40.623 --> 09:41.972
What's going on?

09:42.016 --> 09:44.366
You know,
I haven't seen this guy

09:44.409 --> 09:46.281
since his Little League
coaching days.

09:46.324 --> 09:47.978
And, no,
I was not on the team.

09:48.022 --> 09:49.327
[ Chuckles ] Thank you.

09:49.371 --> 09:51.460
Thank you.

09:51.503 --> 09:53.680
[ Sighs ][ Door opens, bell jingles ]

09:53.723 --> 09:55.769
[ Clears throat ][ Door closes ]

09:55.812 --> 09:59.990
When you decided to surprise me
in my car the other day,

10:00.034 --> 10:01.731
that detective
was following me.

10:01.775 --> 10:03.777
He's got pictures
of us together,

10:03.820 --> 10:06.997
which means
we go wayback now.

10:07.041 --> 10:10.566
Following you? How do you know
he didn't follow you here?

10:10.610 --> 10:12.655
He's caught up with
something else at the moment.

10:14.918 --> 10:16.659
Peter's awake.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.183
♪♪

10:23.623 --> 10:25.712
Man: I remember
answering the door,

10:25.755 --> 10:28.279
and then I couldn't see
anything.

10:28.323 --> 10:31.848
I -- After that, it's all --
it's all a blur.

10:31.892 --> 10:33.807
[ Monitor beeping ]

10:33.850 --> 10:37.114
Man on P.A.:
Neonatal for Dr. Brown...

10:37.158 --> 10:38.768
Neonatal for Dr. Brown.

10:40.117 --> 10:42.467
Do either of these gentlemen
look familiar to you?

10:45.732 --> 10:48.473
No. No, I have no idea
who they are.

10:48.517 --> 10:50.911
You -- You think
these are the --

10:50.954 --> 10:52.347
the guys who broke in?

10:52.390 --> 10:54.436
Neither of them looks familiar?

10:56.960 --> 10:59.093
No.

11:00.790 --> 11:02.662
Wait. I --

11:02.705 --> 11:06.927
I taught that guy's daughter
a -- a couple of years ago.

11:06.970 --> 11:10.539
Um, Layla. I...

11:10.582 --> 11:12.933
I haven't seen him
since her funeral.

11:12.976 --> 11:15.283
It was so sad.
I...

11:15.326 --> 11:17.851
Wait. What -- What does he
have to do with the robbery?

11:20.244 --> 11:22.725
Are you aware
of a podcast

11:22.769 --> 11:25.815
that one of your
former students released

11:25.859 --> 11:27.774
accusing you
of sexual assault?

11:27.817 --> 11:29.950
What?

11:29.993 --> 11:32.692
No. I don't know
what you're talking about.

11:32.735 --> 11:35.564
No one has ever accused me
of anything like that at all.

11:35.607 --> 11:37.131
This guy.

11:37.174 --> 11:40.700
He's friends with the girl who
did the podcast, Sophie Dixon.

11:40.743 --> 11:41.918
Does that jog your memory
at all?

11:41.962 --> 11:43.877
I mean...

11:43.920 --> 11:48.708
Sophie was a student of mine
this last year.

11:48.751 --> 11:51.058
W-What does she have to do
with the attack?

11:51.101 --> 11:52.973
I was hoping
you could tell me.

11:53.016 --> 11:55.192
I told you, I don't remember
anything from that night.

11:55.236 --> 11:56.716
For all I know,
you're the one who broke in.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.413
Nurse: He's not.

11:58.456 --> 12:02.243
But he isthe person who
should let you get some rest.

12:02.286 --> 12:03.766
Yes, of course.

12:03.810 --> 12:09.641
♪♪

12:09.685 --> 12:11.731
I'll circle back once
you've gotten some rest.

12:11.774 --> 12:17.562
♪♪

12:17.606 --> 12:20.304
Oh, my God. Those RadioShack
walkie-talkies were the worst.

12:20.348 --> 12:23.003
Right? They had, like,
a three-foot range!

12:23.046 --> 12:25.440
"Can you hear me?"
[ Imitating static ]

12:25.483 --> 12:27.094
"I can seeyou."
[ Imitating static ]

12:27.137 --> 12:28.835
[ Laughs ]
That is so true.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.445
Hey, Valerie.
Here. Try this.

12:33.709 --> 12:37.539
Oh...my...God. Mm.
That's delicious.

12:37.582 --> 12:39.889
I think you made it wrong.
That's not the recipe, is it?

12:39.933 --> 12:41.412
Well, I --
I might have improv'd

12:41.456 --> 12:43.066
a couple of things
at the end.

12:43.110 --> 12:45.460
Mm. Is that cinnamon? It totally
brings out the flavor --

12:45.503 --> 12:46.809
The flavor
of the beans, right?

12:46.853 --> 12:48.768
Was that on your menu
at Someday?

12:48.811 --> 12:50.421
No, girl. We have been
talking about me all day.

12:50.465 --> 12:51.814
What about you?

12:51.858 --> 12:55.339
What did you do before
you landed this sweet gig?

12:55.383 --> 12:57.298
Ehh. A bit of this,
bit of that.

12:57.341 --> 13:00.692
Before I clocked in at...
the rainforest,

13:00.736 --> 13:02.607
I worked at Roberta's.

13:02.651 --> 13:04.609
On Comm Ave?

13:04.653 --> 13:07.090
I went to culinary school
with their head chef.

13:07.134 --> 13:08.396
Cool.

13:08.439 --> 13:09.789
Where'd you go
to school?

13:09.832 --> 13:13.009
'Cause your technique is...
fantastic.

13:13.053 --> 13:14.402
[ Sighs ]
I actually didn't.

13:14.445 --> 13:16.665
I-I just picked up stuff
along the way.

13:16.708 --> 13:19.450
Edgar, those shoes
are not OSHA-approved.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.409
Look out.
Here comes the Po-po.

13:21.452 --> 13:23.193
This is the second time
I've told you.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.760
Punch out,
go to the store,

13:24.804 --> 13:26.675
and do not come back until
you have the proper footwear!

13:28.590 --> 13:31.332
He's wearing Crocs in a place
called Crocodilze.

13:31.375 --> 13:33.203
How's he not making him
Employee of the Year?

13:33.247 --> 13:34.770
[ Both laugh ]Is there a problem over there?

13:34.814 --> 13:36.076
[ Laughter stops ]

13:36.119 --> 13:37.599
-No. Mnh-mnh.
-No, sir.

13:37.642 --> 13:39.427
Okay.

13:39.470 --> 13:40.950
[ Groans ]

13:40.994 --> 13:43.126
God. I mean...
What a hole.

13:43.170 --> 13:45.476
That's exactly why I want
to own my own place someday,

13:45.520 --> 13:46.913
so I never have to work
for someone.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.176
[ Sighs ]

13:50.742 --> 13:52.832
Oh, I'm so sorry.
I-I didn't mean to.

13:52.875 --> 13:55.269
No, no. It's okay.
You're right.

13:55.312 --> 13:57.314
It's one of the perks I'll miss.
[ Chuckles ]

13:57.358 --> 13:58.750
Still...

13:58.794 --> 14:00.535
[ Imitates static ]
I'm sorry.

14:00.578 --> 14:01.928
[ Imitates static ]
[ Laughs ]

14:01.971 --> 14:03.799
[ Imitates static ]
Not a problem.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.757
[ Imitates static ]
Heh. Heh-heh.

14:05.801 --> 14:07.803
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:07.847 --> 14:09.196
And why'd you valet park?

14:09.239 --> 14:11.111
That's $6.50
you'll never see again.

14:11.154 --> 14:13.635
You're definitely the perfect
person to celebrate with.

14:13.678 --> 14:16.594
I'm just saying. You should be
more careful with your money.

14:16.638 --> 14:18.727
I don't have to be, not with you
stealing all those mints

14:18.770 --> 14:21.251
that's you're gonna...
resell later, I assume?

14:21.295 --> 14:23.036
-Hi, there.
-Hey.

14:23.079 --> 14:25.299
Can we be seated at your
largest table for two, please?

14:25.342 --> 14:27.475
Of course. Follow me.

14:28.911 --> 14:30.826
Why Crocodilze, Pop?

14:30.870 --> 14:33.176
I asked you to choose
someplace great,

14:33.220 --> 14:34.656
'cause I got good news.

14:34.699 --> 14:37.050
With Gina working here,
don't you get a great discount?

14:37.093 --> 14:39.226
Will you stop worrying
about money for two seconds?

14:39.269 --> 14:41.141
As long as you'll
startworrying.

14:41.184 --> 14:43.708
[ Sighs ] Ahh.

14:43.752 --> 14:46.059
The reason that I wanted
to take you to lunch today

14:46.102 --> 14:48.322
is because
I sold my movie.

14:48.365 --> 14:50.672
Okay. Don't get ahead
of yourself.

14:50.715 --> 14:52.848
It's just been chosen
for a festival.

14:52.892 --> 14:55.807
No. No, no. No.
I got the call earlier today.

14:55.851 --> 15:00.812
Paragon Plus previewed my movie,
and they want to buy it.

15:00.856 --> 15:03.293
May I say something,
please?

15:03.337 --> 15:05.165
If you absolutely
have to, yeah.

15:06.731 --> 15:08.864
That is...

15:08.908 --> 15:10.605
incredible.

15:10.648 --> 15:12.476
I'm proud of you, son.

15:12.520 --> 15:14.435
Thanks, Dad.

15:14.478 --> 15:17.960
Now, I assume the sound bite
from my interview

15:18.004 --> 15:19.222
made the final cut?

15:19.266 --> 15:21.311
[ Chuckles ] It did.
Good.

15:21.355 --> 15:23.835
Then I'll just need four tickets
for the premiere.

15:23.879 --> 15:25.315
Four?

15:25.359 --> 15:28.057
Wait. There's you, Flo.
Who else?

15:28.101 --> 15:31.843
Her best friend, Gladys,
and her loser husband, Dan.

15:31.887 --> 15:33.149
He thinks he's famous

15:33.193 --> 15:35.543
'cause he was in one lousy
Denny's commercial.

15:35.586 --> 15:37.675
I'm gonna show him
what fame really is.

15:37.719 --> 15:40.113
[ Laughs ]
You show him, Pop.

15:40.156 --> 15:42.158
Ooh, Claudia.
There you are.

15:42.202 --> 15:44.726
Hey. Can I practice what I want
to say to Jane real quick?

15:44.769 --> 15:46.336
Can we wait till
the show's over?

15:46.380 --> 15:47.555
[ Muffled shouting ]

15:47.598 --> 15:49.122
Uh, what show?

15:49.165 --> 15:51.211
The one happening
in the conference room.

15:51.254 --> 15:53.430
Nick and Jane are in there
right now getting yelled at.

15:53.474 --> 15:55.389
Apparently someone complained
about them creating

15:55.432 --> 15:57.347
"a hostile
work environment."

15:57.391 --> 15:59.175
[Chuckling]
Hostile work envir--

16:00.785 --> 16:02.700
Oh, no.

16:02.744 --> 16:04.572
What?

16:04.615 --> 16:07.879
I think I did something bad.
Real bad.

16:07.923 --> 16:09.403
I think --
I think I'm the one

16:09.446 --> 16:12.014
that made the "hostile
work environment" comment.

16:12.058 --> 16:15.017
I m-- I made a joke to
this woman, Rachel Frumaychar.

16:15.061 --> 16:16.584
She must have said
something.

16:16.627 --> 16:19.065
Rachel Frumaychar?

16:19.108 --> 16:21.284
Her name's not
Rachel Frumaychar.

16:21.328 --> 16:23.243
That's Rachel.
"From HR."

16:23.286 --> 16:25.288
What?! [ Gasps ]

16:25.332 --> 16:27.247
-Suck it.
-Bite me.

16:27.290 --> 16:28.248
[Sweetly]
Have a nice day.

16:28.291 --> 16:30.467
Only if you have
a better one.

16:30.511 --> 16:34.689
♪♪

16:34.732 --> 16:35.733
Oh, my God.

16:40.173 --> 16:41.826
You remember that first
video camera you bought?

16:41.870 --> 16:43.437
Yeah. 8th grade.

16:43.480 --> 16:45.178
Thing was so big,
it had a backpack.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.093
[ Laughs ]
You looked like a Transformer.

16:47.136 --> 16:49.617
[ Laughs ] I did. I worked
all season to pay for that thing

16:49.660 --> 16:51.445
after you convinced Gil to let
me work with you at The Garden.

16:51.488 --> 16:53.577
You never officially
worked there.

16:53.621 --> 16:55.753
Okay, but somehow
after I finished

16:55.797 --> 16:59.018
sweeping up peanut shells
and ice-cream wrappers,

16:59.061 --> 17:02.543
I'd magically find $20 laying
on the ground in Section 327

17:02.586 --> 17:05.154
at the end of my shift.

17:05.198 --> 17:07.287
I remember after one game,

17:07.330 --> 17:10.029
Robert Parish was coming out
of the locker room.

17:10.072 --> 17:12.857
Celts had won, and Parish
was in a great mood.

17:12.901 --> 17:15.469
Guess he'd seen you
cleaning up the place,

17:15.512 --> 17:17.340
and he stopped
and asked me your name.

17:17.384 --> 17:20.126
Even when you were
in 8th grade,

17:20.169 --> 17:23.912
you were already getting
people's attention.

17:23.955 --> 17:26.001
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

17:26.045 --> 17:27.220
Oh.
Yeah, yeah.

17:27.263 --> 17:28.699
Go ahead, take it.

17:28.743 --> 17:30.266
I have to hit the head,
anyways.

17:30.310 --> 17:32.529
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:32.573 --> 17:33.922
Hey. This is Rome.

17:33.965 --> 17:35.489
Rome, this is Austin Felix

17:35.532 --> 17:37.056
from the New England
Film Institute.

17:37.099 --> 17:38.405
Oh, hi.

17:38.448 --> 17:40.537
First of all,
I just wanted to tell you

17:40.581 --> 17:42.670
how much your documentary
resonated with me.

17:42.713 --> 17:44.802
There are so many people
trying to tell

17:44.846 --> 17:48.937
this type of story right now,
but yours is truly unique.

17:48.980 --> 17:50.982
It just sticks with you.

17:51.026 --> 17:52.680
I really appreciate that.
It means a lot.

17:52.723 --> 17:54.551
I just hope our documentary

17:54.595 --> 17:56.945
helps to evoke
some necessary change.

17:56.988 --> 17:59.295
Me too. That's actually
why I'm calling.

17:59.339 --> 18:00.862
I spoke to your agent,

18:00.905 --> 18:03.430
and I know a lot of great things
are happening for you.

18:03.473 --> 18:06.215
I just had to tell you
how disappointed I am

18:06.259 --> 18:08.783
that you've decided to pull
your film from the festival.

18:08.826 --> 18:09.871
What?

18:09.914 --> 18:12.613
Oh, I --
I assumed you knew.

18:12.656 --> 18:15.964
Your agent said
you don't want it shown.

18:16.007 --> 18:17.444
No. I --

18:17.487 --> 18:19.707
T-There must be
some mistake.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.317
Okay. You know what?

18:21.361 --> 18:23.798
Let me talk to him,
and then I'll call you back.

18:23.841 --> 18:25.408
Sure.
Okay.

18:25.452 --> 18:27.106
[ Cellphone beeps ]

18:27.149 --> 18:29.151
♪♪

18:29.195 --> 18:33.242
And that's just it, Pam,
and everyone who is listening.

18:33.286 --> 18:35.244
It's not just about
getting the help you need.

18:35.288 --> 18:39.553
It is about getting
the help you deserve.

18:39.596 --> 18:41.250
You're In the Room
with Dr. Bloom.

18:41.294 --> 18:43.209
We'll be back
after these messages.

18:43.252 --> 18:45.080
Man: This has been
"In the Room"...And we're clear.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.430
Ugh! I can't believe
I got Jane in trouble.

18:47.474 --> 18:49.824
So much for asking
for the job permanently.

18:49.867 --> 18:51.347
[ Scoffs ] Nick and Jane
were in there together,

18:51.391 --> 18:53.044
and Nick just gave you
the piece of cake

18:53.088 --> 18:54.568
with the most frosting
on it.

18:54.611 --> 18:57.484
If he doesn't know it was you,
I-I doubt Jane does, either.

18:57.527 --> 18:59.399
Yes, you're right.
You're right.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.575
What is the deal
with those two, anyway?

19:02.750 --> 19:04.534
Oh, my God.

19:04.578 --> 19:06.188
[ Stammers ]
You don't know?

19:06.232 --> 19:08.495
Nick and Jane
used to date.

19:08.538 --> 19:09.931
Like, each other?

19:09.974 --> 19:11.454
This was back when
she was just a producer

19:11.498 --> 19:13.152
and he hosted a full hour.

19:13.195 --> 19:15.154
I'm sorry.
Nick hosted a full hour?

19:15.197 --> 19:16.546
You're burying
a lot of ledes.

19:16.590 --> 19:19.375
30 seconds to air.Well, talk quickly.

19:19.419 --> 19:21.638
Okay.
A couple of years ago,

19:21.682 --> 19:23.205
Jane was offered the job
of station manager,

19:23.249 --> 19:24.728
but the execs
didn't want a supervisor

19:24.772 --> 19:27.035
dating one of her subordinates,
so she had to choose.

19:27.078 --> 19:28.602
Nick or the promotion.

19:28.645 --> 19:30.343
Yeah, it's been awkward between
the two of them ever since.

19:30.386 --> 19:31.605
Okay. How have you
not told me this?

19:31.648 --> 19:33.476
You tell me random facts
that are irrelevant,

19:33.520 --> 19:35.130
like the front elevator
is slow,

19:35.174 --> 19:37.480
but you didn't tell me that my
boss broke my colleague's heart?

19:37.524 --> 19:39.134
And we're back! You're In the Room
with Dr. Bloom.

19:39.178 --> 19:43.921
This is Dr. Maggie Bloom,
here to listen, here to help.

19:43.965 --> 19:46.185
[ Clicking, beep ]

19:46.228 --> 19:48.274
[ Line ringing]

19:50.276 --> 19:51.712
Nurse: ICU.

19:51.755 --> 19:56.238
Hi, there. My name is...
Sebastian Benoit.

19:56.282 --> 19:57.892
My cousin Peter
is a patient there.

19:57.935 --> 20:00.721
I'm just calling
to see how he's doing.

20:00.764 --> 20:03.550
I'm sorry, sir, but
we're not allowed to discuss

20:03.593 --> 20:04.942
a patient's
medical condition

20:04.986 --> 20:06.553
with anyone other than
immediate family.

20:06.596 --> 20:08.163
Yeah, I-I totally
get that.

20:08.207 --> 20:11.035
Uh, like I said,
he is my cousin.

20:11.079 --> 20:14.125
Uh, his wife texted us
to say that he was awake.

20:14.169 --> 20:16.171
Uh, I know she's trying
to stay positive,

20:16.215 --> 20:19.261
and I didn't want
to ask her if...

20:19.305 --> 20:23.134
you know, if -- if we needed to
visit as soon as possible or...

20:23.178 --> 20:25.136
Oh. Yeah.

20:25.180 --> 20:26.877
[ Elevator bell dings,
doors open ]

20:28.183 --> 20:30.794
Well, you should know

20:30.838 --> 20:32.753
he's actually doing quite well
physically.

20:32.796 --> 20:35.669
He's out of any grave danger.

20:35.712 --> 20:40.195
Oh, my God. That's --
That's wonderful news.

20:40.239 --> 20:42.719
If you do come,

20:42.763 --> 20:45.635
don't be thrown
if he forgets things.

20:45.679 --> 20:49.465
He's having severe
short-term memory loss.

20:51.946 --> 20:53.034
Wow.

20:55.602 --> 20:57.430
Thank you
for letting me know.

20:57.473 --> 20:59.301
♪♪

20:59.345 --> 21:00.824
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:00.868 --> 21:02.043
[ Knock on window ]

21:02.086 --> 21:03.305
Hey!
Whoa!

21:03.349 --> 21:05.264
I guilted her
into onion rings, too!

21:05.307 --> 21:07.135
My man! All right!

21:07.178 --> 21:10.094
Well, let's go inside and
ring-toss them into my mouth!

21:10.138 --> 21:11.095
[ Chuckles ]

21:13.359 --> 21:16.884
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:16.927 --> 21:18.364
[ Door opens ]

21:18.407 --> 21:19.800
Eddie:
Okay. Thank you.

21:19.843 --> 21:22.455
[ Grunts ] Hi.

21:22.498 --> 21:25.066
Um, I'm meeting someone here.
Thanks.

21:25.109 --> 21:29.244
♪♪

21:29.288 --> 21:31.159
[ Door closes ]

21:31.202 --> 21:35.642
♪♪

21:35.685 --> 21:37.470
Eddie: Um...

21:37.513 --> 21:43.824
♪♪

21:43.867 --> 21:45.304
[ Chair legs slide ]

21:45.347 --> 21:46.653
[ Grunts ]

21:46.696 --> 21:52.049
♪♪

21:52.093 --> 21:54.051
[ Eddie sighs ]

21:55.531 --> 21:57.098
Well, you wanted to talk.

21:57.141 --> 21:59.579
[ Breathing sharply ]

22:01.015 --> 22:02.669
So talk.

22:07.717 --> 22:09.632
[ Indistinct conversations ]

22:13.201 --> 22:15.508
[ Sighs ]

22:15.551 --> 22:18.206
I was driving, and I --

22:18.249 --> 22:20.774
I was distracted. I should have
been paying attention.

22:24.995 --> 22:26.780
I'm so sorry.

22:31.132 --> 22:33.177
Do they know
if you're going to --

22:33.221 --> 22:35.528
Oh, I'm gonna be in this chair
for the rest of my life.

22:43.144 --> 22:46.713
I know this doesn't make up
for what I did,

22:46.756 --> 22:49.150
but please...take it.

22:49.193 --> 22:50.325
It's all that I have.

22:51.370 --> 22:54.938
I don't want your money.

22:54.982 --> 22:56.462
And I certainly
don't want your pity.

22:56.505 --> 23:05.296
♪♪

23:05.340 --> 23:13.914
♪♪

23:13.957 --> 23:17.004
My husband
has a temper.

23:17.047 --> 23:21.051
And when he gets upset,
he lashes out.

23:21.095 --> 23:25.926
Frank came home in a bad place
that night.

23:25.969 --> 23:28.363
Something happened
at work.

23:28.407 --> 23:31.888
A coworker disrespected him
in front of his boss.

23:31.932 --> 23:35.022
It doesn't matter.

23:35.065 --> 23:38.939
But I knew just by the way
he put his keys down

23:38.982 --> 23:41.724
that I had to get us
out of there,

23:41.768 --> 23:45.859
so I grabbed one of Julian's
applesauce tubes,

23:45.902 --> 23:50.472
and I put him in the car seat,
and we went for a drive.

23:50.516 --> 23:54.650
I thought that if we were out
for maybe an hour or so,

23:54.694 --> 23:57.261
by the time we came back,

23:57.305 --> 24:00.700
Frank would have had
a-a couple drinks,

24:00.743 --> 24:02.310
maybe even be passed out.

24:05.748 --> 24:07.315
But Julian dropped
his applesauce,

24:07.358 --> 24:10.057
and it slid under
the passenger seat, and I...

24:10.100 --> 24:12.059
I reached for it.

24:12.102 --> 24:13.582
♪♪

24:13.626 --> 24:17.630
I took my eyes off the road
for two seconds.

24:17.673 --> 24:19.588
And that's when...

24:22.417 --> 24:23.679
God.

24:25.333 --> 24:26.682
[ Sniffles ]

24:26.726 --> 24:28.684
[ Breathes deeply ]

24:30.991 --> 24:33.210
[Voice breaking]
I wanted to turn myself in,

24:33.254 --> 24:34.951
but if I did,

24:34.995 --> 24:39.260
Frankie would be the one
to look after Julian.

24:39.303 --> 24:41.175
I couldn't let that happen.

24:41.218 --> 24:47.616
♪♪

24:47.660 --> 24:49.923
I'm in recovery, too.

24:51.272 --> 24:56.233
I was almost, uh,
12 years sober...

24:56.277 --> 24:59.193
but I relapsed
after the, uh...

24:59.236 --> 25:03.240
♪♪

25:03.284 --> 25:04.546
[ Sighs ]

25:04.590 --> 25:08.376
♪♪

25:08.419 --> 25:09.899
Listen.

25:11.292 --> 25:14.034
You didn't ruin my life.

25:14.077 --> 25:15.383
[ Crying ]

25:15.426 --> 25:18.865
You know, I think
what's best for both of us

25:18.908 --> 25:22.216
is to...

25:22.259 --> 25:26.786
just take the hands
that we've been dealt...

25:26.829 --> 25:29.310
and move on.

25:29.353 --> 25:35.577
♪♪

25:35.621 --> 25:38.188
I'm sorry.

25:38.232 --> 25:40.843
I --
I am so sorry.

25:40.887 --> 25:44.978
♪♪

25:45.021 --> 25:47.502
No. Hey! Wait! Hey!

25:47.546 --> 25:49.591
♪♪

25:49.635 --> 25:51.593
[ Sighs ]

25:51.637 --> 26:00.559
♪♪

26:00.602 --> 26:01.734
[ Envelope thuds ]

26:01.777 --> 26:03.562
[ Sighs ]

26:03.605 --> 26:06.782
Rome, the reason why we
pulled out of the festival

26:06.826 --> 26:09.480
is because Paragon Plus didn't
want people seeing the movie

26:09.524 --> 26:11.221
before it premiered
on their platform.

26:11.265 --> 26:12.440
I get that. Okay?

26:12.483 --> 26:14.790
But isn't the festival
a great opportunity?

26:14.834 --> 26:16.705
Listen. [ Chuckles ]

26:16.749 --> 26:19.360
You do festivals
to get these offers.

26:19.403 --> 26:21.492
You let me handle
the business side, okay?

26:21.536 --> 26:23.930
We closed the deal.You're right.

26:23.973 --> 26:27.020
So go somewhere great
and celebrate.

26:27.063 --> 26:29.588
I'm already there.

26:29.631 --> 26:31.372
Okay.

26:31.415 --> 26:33.940
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:33.983 --> 26:37.291
♪♪

26:37.334 --> 26:39.380
[ Line rings]

26:39.423 --> 26:41.904
Hey, Austin. It's Rome.

26:41.948 --> 26:44.037
Look, man, I just got off
the phone with my agent,

26:44.080 --> 26:47.127
and he said the streamer
who bought my movie

26:47.170 --> 26:49.869
wants to show it exclusively
on theirplatform.

26:49.912 --> 26:52.088
Look, man, I'm sorry
about the festival.

26:52.132 --> 26:54.047
I was really
looking forward to it.

26:54.090 --> 26:56.745
By any chance, was the streamer
you sold your film to

26:56.789 --> 26:58.399
Paragon Plus?

26:58.442 --> 27:00.706
Yeah. How'd you know?

27:00.749 --> 27:05.232
Rome, I hate to tell you this,
but they're doing a documentary

27:05.275 --> 27:07.495
on the same topic
with Trevor Jones.

27:07.538 --> 27:08.931
No. No.
Y-You're mistaken, bro.

27:08.975 --> 27:10.846
I-If they had one
with a huge,

27:10.890 --> 27:12.587
big-name director
like Trevor Jones,

27:12.631 --> 27:13.719
why would they want mine?

27:13.762 --> 27:15.416
So they can control it,

27:15.459 --> 27:18.201
keep it from upstaging
their more high-profile movie.

27:18.245 --> 27:20.856
No. Y-You sure?

27:20.900 --> 27:22.728
You don't pull a film
from a festival.

27:22.771 --> 27:25.731
You show it and get
the whole town talking.

27:25.774 --> 27:28.255
It just feels like
a catch-and-kill.

27:28.298 --> 27:30.126
I'm sorry.

27:30.170 --> 27:33.390
♪♪

27:33.434 --> 27:36.002
Gary: No! [ Laughs ]
Come on!It is soa real sport.

