had a dog named Pickles.

27:38.657 --> 27:41.268
Okay, just because some moron
gave his dog an unfortunate name

27:41.311 --> 27:44.227
doesn't mean that pickleball
is a sport.

27:44.271 --> 27:46.403
It's the fastest-growing
sport in America.

27:46.447 --> 27:48.362
Open your mind.[ Laughs ] Okay.

27:48.405 --> 27:49.972
Let's check the park
close to our new house

27:50.016 --> 27:51.452
and see if it has courts.Great.

27:51.495 --> 27:54.281
You do that while I finish
this e-mail to the broker.

27:54.324 --> 27:57.893
Dude, today is the day we lift
contingencies on the house.

27:57.937 --> 27:59.242
We just need
the sewer-line report, man.

27:59.286 --> 28:00.722
Isn't that exciting?

28:00.766 --> 28:02.724
You're saying words,
but they don't mean anything.

28:02.768 --> 28:04.117
Ha ha! That's fair.[ Laptop dings ]

28:04.160 --> 28:07.686
What? Darce, I just got
an e-mail from my agent

28:07.729 --> 28:10.427
that the offer that's coming
for the condo is all cash.

28:10.471 --> 28:12.125
Can you believe that?

28:12.168 --> 28:14.736
Ahh! It's all
coming together.

28:14.780 --> 28:18.653
Great. Um, all I need
is a nine-letter word

28:18.697 --> 28:20.873
for a well-behaved
little boy.

28:20.916 --> 28:22.570
Is that where your head
has been this whole time,

28:22.613 --> 28:23.745
in a --
in a crossword puzzle?

28:23.789 --> 28:25.007
Boo!

28:25.051 --> 28:26.705
All right, uh,
well-behaved little boy.

28:26.748 --> 28:28.315
Well, we know
it's not this kid.

28:28.358 --> 28:30.709
Oh, no.
Unless your name
is Liammmmmm.

28:30.752 --> 28:32.362
Umm-umm...No. Nope. Not a name.

28:32.406 --> 28:33.886
Umm...
That's not a name.

28:33.929 --> 28:35.191
What? Open your mind.

28:35.235 --> 28:36.976
People spell things
weird sometimes,

28:37.019 --> 28:38.804
like European-style,
right?

28:43.069 --> 28:45.027
You've never had
a Snoopy sno-cone machine?!

28:45.071 --> 28:47.029
I mean,
I've had a sno-cone.

28:47.073 --> 28:48.814
That's not the same thing.

28:48.857 --> 28:52.165
Gina. Regina! Did you
make the chili today?

28:52.208 --> 28:53.862
Um...why?

28:53.906 --> 28:56.343
Because whoever did
did notfollow the recipe.

28:56.386 --> 28:58.432
This is exactly why
I was hesitant to hire you.

28:58.475 --> 28:59.999
I knew you'd walk around
acting like

29:00.042 --> 29:01.435
you're better
than all of us.

29:01.478 --> 29:04.046
I cannot have you undermining
the Crocodilze way.

29:04.090 --> 29:06.875
It was me.
I made the chili.

29:06.919 --> 29:08.616
I just thought cinnamon

29:08.659 --> 29:10.923
would bring out
the flavor of the beans.

29:10.966 --> 29:13.186
Did you try it?
It tastes so much better.

29:13.229 --> 29:15.057
That is not the point.

29:15.101 --> 29:16.667
You're not here to
make things taste better.

29:18.365 --> 29:21.237
Well, you know what I mean.

29:21.281 --> 29:23.370
Do it again,
and you're fired.

29:24.719 --> 29:25.807
Thank you.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.983
You'd do the same thing
for me.

29:28.027 --> 29:30.856
[ Sighs ] Yeah.
Clarice must have loved you.

29:30.899 --> 29:32.422
Who's Clarice?

29:32.466 --> 29:34.337
My friend.

29:34.381 --> 29:36.818
The head chef
at Roberta's?

29:36.862 --> 29:39.647
Oh. Yeah, of course.

29:39.690 --> 29:41.780
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:47.263 --> 29:48.699
Listen.

29:50.527 --> 29:52.921
I lied
on my application.

29:52.965 --> 29:55.837
I-I just needed something
to put on my résumé.

29:55.881 --> 29:57.665
This is my first gig
since I've been out.

30:00.320 --> 30:02.452
I got assigned to kitchen duty
when I was in prison.

30:04.759 --> 30:06.848
That's why you're so good
at cooking

30:06.892 --> 30:08.981
for large groups of people.Yep.

30:09.024 --> 30:11.331
This isn't the first
maximum-security facility

30:11.374 --> 30:13.594
I've worked for.

30:13.637 --> 30:14.987
Uh...

30:15.030 --> 30:18.033
I was in for making some
bad credit-card charges.

30:18.077 --> 30:21.776
I messed up, but I pled guilty
and I served my time.

30:21.820 --> 30:22.864
Does...?

30:22.908 --> 30:25.258
No. Please don't
say anything.

30:26.912 --> 30:29.828
About your
cinnamon trick?

30:29.871 --> 30:32.091
Your secret's safe
with me.

30:32.134 --> 30:33.440
Thanks.

30:35.398 --> 30:36.747
[ Cellphone beeps ]

30:36.791 --> 30:39.707
You know, I wonder if we should
split a piece of pie

30:39.750 --> 30:42.101
so that I can fit into my suit
for the premiere.

30:42.144 --> 30:43.276
Hey, Dad, listen --

30:43.319 --> 30:45.234
You're right.
I'm buying a new one.

30:45.278 --> 30:49.151
I'll just get a bigger size.
Pie me!

30:49.195 --> 30:51.414
No. Pop...

30:51.458 --> 30:54.417
There's not gonna be
a premiere.

30:54.461 --> 30:56.811
What are you talking about?
You sold it.

30:56.855 --> 30:58.944
I did, but apparently
the people who bought it

30:58.987 --> 31:00.989
didn't buy it
because they liked it.

31:01.033 --> 31:03.687
They bought it because
it reminded them of

31:03.731 --> 31:06.168
another documentary
that they like even more,

31:06.212 --> 31:08.431
so they want to keep people
from seeing mine

31:08.475 --> 31:10.172
to ensure
people see theirs.

31:10.216 --> 31:11.957
Sorry. I know you were
excited for the premiere.

31:16.178 --> 31:18.006
You know that day
when Robert Parish

31:18.050 --> 31:20.487
asked me your name?

31:20.530 --> 31:23.533
He asked me my name, too.

31:23.577 --> 31:25.405
I had worked at The Garden
at that point

31:25.448 --> 31:28.321
for almost 19 years.

31:28.364 --> 31:30.410
That was the first time
a player cared enough

31:30.453 --> 31:32.891
to ask me who I was.

31:32.934 --> 31:36.285
And the onlyreason he did

31:36.329 --> 31:39.462
was 'cause
I was yourdad.

31:39.506 --> 31:43.684
Telling Robert Parish
all about you...

31:43.727 --> 31:45.860
I didn't think I'd ever
be more proud of you.

31:47.818 --> 31:50.560
But I am right now.

31:50.604 --> 31:53.215
'Cause just like that 8th grader
that worked all summer

31:53.259 --> 31:56.958
so he could buy that camera
and tell his stories,

31:57.002 --> 31:59.134
you're still doing
what you love.

32:01.267 --> 32:03.834
And don't you ever stop.

32:05.662 --> 32:09.318
Don't take this
the wrong way, Pop...

32:09.362 --> 32:12.452
but you're a lot nicer
at thisrestaurant.

32:12.495 --> 32:14.889
[ Both laugh ]

32:17.674 --> 32:20.155
Okay. All right.
Scale of 1 to 10,

32:20.199 --> 32:22.810
how concerned are you
that your child is obsessed

32:22.853 --> 32:26.466
with a game where the median age
of the player is 85?

32:30.296 --> 32:32.515
Uh-oh.

32:32.559 --> 32:35.127
What's --
What's going on here?

32:36.911 --> 32:38.739
It wasn't a real
crossword clue, Gary.

32:38.782 --> 32:41.002
I made it up.

32:41.046 --> 32:42.656
To quote your son,

32:42.699 --> 32:44.832
you're saying words, but
they don't mean anything.

32:46.007 --> 32:47.748
The night
Peter was attacked,

32:47.791 --> 32:51.012
you said you were at your dad's
watching "Jeopardy!"

32:51.056 --> 32:52.535
Yeah, that's right.

32:52.579 --> 32:55.799
But you've been acting weird
ever since,

32:55.843 --> 32:58.889
so I went back and
I-I watched that episode,

32:58.933 --> 33:01.675
and the final clue was
"This 1883 classic

33:01.718 --> 33:04.112
ends with the words
'A well-behaved little boy.'"

33:08.682 --> 33:10.945
Do you have any idea
what that is, Gary?

33:14.079 --> 33:16.037
It's "Pinocchio."

33:17.734 --> 33:19.998
I'd ask you if you were really
at your dad's that night,

33:20.041 --> 33:22.565
but I'm afraid if you told me
you were, your nose would grow.

33:24.002 --> 33:27.353
So I -- I didn't memorize
the Final Jeopardy! clue?

33:27.396 --> 33:29.355
Darce, this was li--
It was two weeks ago.

33:29.398 --> 33:31.313
Yeah, and ever since,
you've been acting like

33:31.357 --> 33:33.750
you're hiding something.

33:33.794 --> 33:36.623
I-I came home that night,
and Colin was here by himself.

33:38.233 --> 33:40.366
You never leave him alone
that long,

33:40.409 --> 33:43.847
and -- and when I couldn't
reach you, I left you --

33:43.891 --> 33:45.240
I left you a message saying

33:45.284 --> 33:48.113
that I wanted to have a baby
with you,

33:48.156 --> 33:49.766
and you never responded.

33:49.810 --> 33:52.682
These are just
coincidences, okay?Really?

33:52.726 --> 33:55.250
Was it a coincidence
that the guy who stopped by

33:55.294 --> 33:57.383
to ask you about street hockey
was a cop?

33:57.426 --> 34:00.560
♪♪

34:00.603 --> 34:01.909
[ Sighs ]

34:01.952 --> 34:03.084
♪♪

34:03.128 --> 34:04.520
[ Voice breaking ]
Believe me, Gary,

34:04.564 --> 34:07.567
I keep trying to push this away,
but I-I can't.

34:09.308 --> 34:11.179
I don't think
we can do this.

34:13.094 --> 34:15.009
You don't think
we can do what, Darce?

34:15.053 --> 34:19.361
♪♪

34:19.405 --> 34:21.276
What can't we do?

34:23.974 --> 34:26.151
We can't buy this house
together. I'm sorry.

34:26.194 --> 34:27.891
No, no, no. Shh, shh.
Please, please, please.

34:27.935 --> 34:30.807
Don't say that.
Don't say that. Don't say that.

34:30.851 --> 34:33.636
Peter doesn't remember
anything, okay? He --

34:33.680 --> 34:35.116
Oh, my God.No, no, no. No, no, no.

34:35.160 --> 34:37.075
It's gonna be okay, right?
He -- He --

34:37.118 --> 34:38.859
No, it's not.
It's not gonna be okay.

34:38.902 --> 34:39.860
He can't remember what
happened. He can't --It's not gonna be okay!

34:39.903 --> 34:41.209
It's notgonna be okay!

34:41.253 --> 34:44.995
Gary, how could you
have done this to us?

34:45.039 --> 34:46.910
We're gonna move to Lenox.No. Sorry.

34:46.954 --> 34:48.956
The three of us.
I-It's a fresh start.
No.

34:48.999 --> 34:52.438
I cannot have that
around Liam.

34:52.481 --> 34:54.962
What if six months from now
Peter suddenly doesremember?

34:55.005 --> 34:57.138
What -- What if that cop comes
in the middle of the night

34:57.182 --> 34:59.053
and drags you out in handcuffs?
Liam can't see that.

34:59.097 --> 35:00.576
That's not gonna happen.Look, Gary.

35:00.620 --> 35:04.624
[ Crying ] I really, really
want this so badly. I do.

35:04.667 --> 35:06.930
And I love you.

35:06.974 --> 35:08.932
I love you so much,
but...

35:12.240 --> 35:14.024
But I-I can't.

35:14.068 --> 35:15.635
Not after everything
that I've been through.

35:15.678 --> 35:16.940
I live every...

35:18.551 --> 35:20.248
[ Sniffles ]

35:20.292 --> 35:21.771
[Voice breaking] I live every
moment of my life on edge

35:21.815 --> 35:23.643
as it is.

35:23.686 --> 35:25.166
I can't do this.

35:25.210 --> 35:26.950
I didn't go there to hurt him,
all right? I swear to you --

35:26.994 --> 35:28.430
Stop, stop, stop!
Don't tell me anything.

35:28.474 --> 35:31.041
Don't say anything
about that night, okay?

35:31.085 --> 35:33.566
As far as I'm concerned,
you were at your dad's.

35:33.609 --> 35:36.351
You were watching
"Jeopardy!"

35:36.395 --> 35:37.787
Okay?

35:37.831 --> 35:39.702
And if anyone asks you
about the final clue,

35:39.746 --> 35:42.444
know that the answer
is "Pinocchio."

35:42.488 --> 35:50.496
♪♪

35:50.539 --> 35:58.547
♪♪

35:58.591 --> 36:00.201
[ Sighs ]

36:00.245 --> 36:05.119
♪♪

36:05.163 --> 36:10.124
♪♪

36:10.168 --> 36:11.212
[ Sniffles ]

36:13.432 --> 36:15.260
I'm so sorry.

36:18.480 --> 36:21.179
No, you're not.

36:21.222 --> 36:23.572
'Cause you didn't do
anything.

36:23.616 --> 36:28.925
♪♪

36:28.969 --> 36:34.104
♪♪

36:37.456 --> 36:39.806
And then in the second hour,
you wanted to stop

36:39.849 --> 36:41.460
taking calls after
the last commercial break?

36:41.503 --> 36:43.288
Yeah. I just want to
say goodbye, you know?

36:43.331 --> 36:45.899
Thank the listeners.

36:45.942 --> 36:47.248
[ Water pouring ]

36:47.292 --> 36:49.163
Or you could...

36:53.428 --> 36:54.864
Night.

36:54.908 --> 36:57.432
[ Sighs ]

36:57.476 --> 36:59.739
Hear that? She said, "Night,"
not even, "Goodnight."

36:59.782 --> 37:01.828
She knows it was me.

37:02.829 --> 37:05.397
Can I ask a question?

37:05.440 --> 37:08.356
What would you tell yourself
if you were one of your callers?

37:10.532 --> 37:12.404
I would say there's nothing
you're going to regret more

37:12.447 --> 37:14.101
than not taking this chance.

37:15.885 --> 37:17.496
But it's too late.
She's already gone.

37:18.932 --> 37:21.151
Hey. I didn't tell you
Nick and Jane were dating.

37:21.195 --> 37:22.892
I didn't mention
Rachel Frumaychar

37:22.936 --> 37:25.330
was actually
Rachel from HR.

37:25.373 --> 37:27.897
What's the one irrelevant fact
I told you?

37:29.334 --> 37:32.511
That the front elevator
is really slow.

37:34.339 --> 37:35.949
Which is notirrelevant
at all.

37:35.992 --> 37:38.517
Go. It's slow,
but i-it's not thatslow.

37:40.432 --> 37:42.999
Jane! Jane.
Wait. Um...

37:43.043 --> 37:45.306
Before you leave,
I just wanted to say

37:45.350 --> 37:47.439
I know tomorrow is supposed to
be my last show,

37:47.482 --> 37:49.267
but I would love
to be considered

37:49.310 --> 37:51.617
for the position
permanently.

37:51.660 --> 37:53.183
I've loved
these last two weeks,

37:53.227 --> 37:56.099
and I-I just don't
want them to end.

37:56.143 --> 37:59.189
I was wondering when you were
gonna say something.

37:59.233 --> 38:01.235
Maggie, I think you should
definitely be in the running.

38:01.279 --> 38:02.758
In fact,
you'll be happy to know

38:02.802 --> 38:04.151
you are already
on my short list.

38:04.194 --> 38:06.066
[ Breathes sharply ]

38:06.109 --> 38:09.678
Tomorrow, we get the results
back from audience testing.

38:09.722 --> 38:11.114
Test results?

38:11.158 --> 38:13.334
We've been doing them
for the last two weeks.

38:13.378 --> 38:16.729
I wanted to track how you're
doing with our listeners.

38:16.772 --> 38:18.731
I'll be curious to see
what the results say

38:18.774 --> 38:20.689
about how you are
at talking topeople

38:20.733 --> 38:22.561
instead of
talking aboutthem.

38:22.604 --> 38:28.262
♪♪

38:28.306 --> 38:29.307
[ Sighs ]

38:30.656 --> 38:33.311
Hey, sweetie. Can we talk
to you about something?

38:33.354 --> 38:35.487
Is it about
the pickleball courts?

38:35.530 --> 38:38.838
'Cause I couldn't find any
near our house.

38:38.881 --> 38:41.841
[ John Mayer's "I Guess
I Just Feel Like" plays ]

38:41.884 --> 38:44.060
It's not about
pickleball, pal.

38:44.104 --> 38:46.454
♪♪

38:46.498 --> 38:48.413
We're s-still gonna play,
though, right?

38:48.456 --> 38:50.502
♪ I guess I just feel like

38:50.545 --> 38:52.242
Here, sweetie.
Sit down.

38:52.286 --> 38:54.419
[ Gary clears throat ]

38:54.462 --> 38:57.378
♪ Nobody's honest

38:57.422 --> 38:59.467
♪ Nobody's true

38:59.511 --> 39:03.515
For starters, you know that
your mother loves you and...

39:03.558 --> 39:05.691
♪ To make it on through

39:05.734 --> 39:09.695
Dad, when you're walking again,
can we play pickleball?

39:09.738 --> 39:12.219
Liam won't stop
talking about it.

39:12.262 --> 39:15.309
♪ I'm the same way, too

39:15.353 --> 39:17.398
Um...

39:17.442 --> 39:19.792
[ Clears throat ]
Listen, pal.

39:19.835 --> 39:21.837
I need to talk to you
about something.

39:23.535 --> 39:26.059
No, no, no. It's okay.
It's -- It's not a bad thing.

39:26.102 --> 39:27.452
♪♪

39:27.495 --> 39:29.018
[ Sighs ]

39:29.062 --> 39:30.411
♪♪

39:30.455 --> 39:32.979
♪ I guess I just feel like [ Sighs ]

39:33.022 --> 39:36.156
I just need you
to know that...

39:36.199 --> 39:40.639
I am gonna be
in a wheelchair forever.

39:40.682 --> 39:42.205
You don't know that
for sure.

39:42.249 --> 39:45.948
The doctors said there's like
a 7% chance you'll get better.

39:45.992 --> 39:49.343
♪♪

39:49.387 --> 39:51.084
Pull up a chair, buddy.[ Patting on chair ]

39:51.127 --> 39:52.738
[ Clears throat ]

39:52.781 --> 39:55.697
♪♪

39:55.741 --> 39:58.004
T...

39:58.047 --> 40:01.311
I am never
going to walk again.

40:02.748 --> 40:05.794
But that is okay.

40:05.838 --> 40:08.754
Because even though
I can't use my legs,

40:08.797 --> 40:10.364
my life is happier now

40:10.408 --> 40:14.803
than it has been
in a long time...

40:14.847 --> 40:17.110
because I know you love me

40:17.153 --> 40:19.286
and I know
you know I love you.

40:20.896 --> 40:23.464
You know, if this year
has taught us anything,

40:23.508 --> 40:26.467
it's that
when we look around,

40:26.511 --> 40:29.383
we see people who have it
so much harder than we do.

40:29.427 --> 40:31.080
I mean, look at us.

40:31.124 --> 40:34.388
We have this
great new apartment.

40:34.432 --> 40:36.042
You have Legos.

40:37.522 --> 40:40.176
You've got a great crush
who likes you right back,

40:40.220 --> 40:42.135
who I'm not
teasing you about.

40:42.178 --> 40:43.963
♪♪

40:44.006 --> 40:47.227
And most importantly...

40:47.270 --> 40:48.489
we have each other.

40:48.533 --> 40:52.450
♪♪

40:52.493 --> 40:55.104
Now all we need to do
is get youa crush.

40:55.148 --> 40:56.976
I mean, you could double
with me and Kiana,

40:57.019 --> 40:58.456
but if it's just
the three of us,

40:58.499 --> 41:00.109
you're gonna feel like
a third wheel.

41:00.153 --> 41:01.328
I think so.

41:01.371 --> 41:02.808
And bad pun.
Get out of here.

41:02.851 --> 41:03.939
[ Giggles ]

41:03.983 --> 41:06.420
♪ I guess I just feel like

41:06.464 --> 41:09.510
♪♪

41:09.554 --> 41:11.904
♪ Good things are gone

41:11.947 --> 41:13.775
♪♪

41:13.819 --> 41:14.994
It's just
you and me again, pal.

41:15.037 --> 41:18.563
♪ And the weight of my worries

41:18.606 --> 41:21.217
Sorry.

41:21.261 --> 41:23.568
[ Sighs ]♪ Is too much to take on

